# TailwindCSS v3 At-Rules

This project uses **TailwindCSS v3** for styling. The following custom CSS at-rules and directives are **VALID** and should not be flagged as errors:

## Valid TailwindCSS At-Rules

### `@tailwind`

Used to inject Tailwind's base, components, utilities, and variants styles into your CSS.

```css
@tailwind base;
@tailwind components;
@tailwind utilities;
```

### `@apply`

Used to inline any existing utility classes into your own custom CSS.

```css
.btn-primary {
	@apply bg-blue-500 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded;
}
```

### `@layer`

Used to tell Tailwind which "bucket" a set of custom styles belong to.

```css
@layer components {
	.card {
		@apply rounded-lg shadow-md p-4;
	}
}
```

### `@screen`

Used to create media queries that reference your breakpoints by name.

```css
@screen sm {
	.custom-class {
		@apply text-lg;
	}
}
```

### `@variants`

Used to generate responsive, hover, focus, and other variants of your own utilities.

```css
@variants hover, focus {
	.custom-utility {
		@apply bg-black;
	}
}
```

### `@responsive`

Used to generate responsive variants (deprecated in v3 but may still exist in legacy code).

## Theme Function

The `theme()` function is also valid for accessing Tailwind config values:

```css
.element {
	color: theme('colors.blue.500');
}
```

## Project Context

- All SCSS files in `assets/css/` may use these at-rules
- All Vue files in `/components/` and `/pages/` may use these at-rules
- These are part of TailwindCSS v3 and should be treated as valid syntax
- The build process will properly transpile these directives
